09/04/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The daily <I>Vjesnik</I> quoted diplomatic sources as saying that The Hague war crimes tribunal suspended the arrest warrant for Croatian retired Gen Janko Bobetko on Monday (7 April). 
A panel of judges reportedly annulled the extradition order, acknowledging documents Croatia sent in response to the indictment and the results of a medical exam of the 84-year-old general.
In other news, the Vatican confirmed on Tuesday that Pope John Paul II will visit Croatia in early June. 
Stops are planned in Rijeka, Zadar, Dubrovnik, Osijek and Djakovo. 
(Vjesnik - 09/04/03; HINA - 08/04/03
